Steps to connect Tableau and set up the data source. 8

1.       Open the Tableau then

2.      Click on Microsoft SQL Server 

3.       Write the name of the server you want to connect to.  E.g. (DESKTOP-HDCOE7T\CB2016SQLSERVER).

4.       Click sign In.

5.       Select a database name.  E.g. (DataWarehouse).

6.       Drag and drop table/viewâ€™s (E.g. - vw_Zendesk data) on the worksheet.

7.       Click Update Now.

After creating data source, the tableau data source  looks like  the  screen shot below.
